# Applies to `docker build -f server/Dockerfile .` (repo root context) —
# without this, the build would tar up the whole 13+ GB monorepo (server/.venv/
# alone is ~12 GB; DA3METRIC-LARGE.onnx is 698 MB; client/ is 754 MB).

.git
client
depth-anything-3
onnx_models
paddle_ocr_server
test_module
ros2-depth-anything-v3-trt
DA3METRIC-LARGE.onnx
docker-compose.yml
Dockerfile
setup.sh
navigation-state.md
CLAUDE.md

# Only server/tools/depth.py's optional DEPTH_MODEL=da3 path and
# server/grpc_server.py's DA3-ONNX walking mode need anything from scan_server/,
# and only da3_wrapper.py — the rest (VIO/GTSAM, mvs.py, map exporting) is
# Scan Server-only tooling, never imported by the live server.
scan_server/*
!scan_server/da3_wrapper.py

server/.venv
server/__pycache__
server/**/__pycache__
server/.env
server/gt.py
server/_archived
server/data
